description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, tech-savvy and creative Digital Media Assistant to join our growing, award-winning Corporate Communications Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek an individual with the skills to help us communicate and connect with our large and diverse population via our digital channels. This fixed-term post will play a key part in the further development of our internet, intranet and social media channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have some communications/PR experience and a solid understanding of web, CMS and social media and related analytic tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They must also be confident in using Microsoft Office packages and video editing software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 12 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel Starkey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Digital Communications Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rachel.starkey@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
